{"title":"Extra parameters","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Extra parameters","date":"2010-06-07","author":"Fulton, Beth (Environment, Hobart)"},"headingText":"harvest.prm","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\nIn tinkering with bioeconomic and assessment code I've added at least the following a probably a few more 9sorry if I missed any)\n\n\nUpdateMaxSalePrice    0          Whether want to dynamically update maximum sale price as prices change through time (1) or not (0) - if the later than making it a lowest acceptable threshold in effect\n\n###### assess.prm\n\ntClassicalAssessStart 3650     # Day of run to start assessments\n\n###### economics.prm\n\nOrigEconCalc 0 Whether to use the original economic driver calculation (1) or use one that is total price - total cost\n\nhist_only         1   Whether use historic effort distribution (1) or dynamic based on economics (0)\n  \nhist_only_timeout 1824 Day of run with hist_only is set back to 0 (so more dynamic effort allocation used) - currently assumed to be around end/start of calendar year\n  \nDVstart          1880 Day of run when management using deemed values starts\n  \nTaxStart          366666666660 Day of run when management using taxzes starts\n  \nUseVPUE           1    Flag to indicate whether using CPUE (0) or VPUE (1) to dictate effort distributions\n\n## Bycatch incentives flags\n\n  \nUsingEffortIncentive    0    Whether using effort-based incentives (0=no, 1=yes)(if want to use ITE)\n  \nBycatchCountDiscards    1    Whether bycatch counted in discards (0=no, 1-yes)(1)\n  \nTemporalBycatchAvoid    1    Whether taking temporal exposure to bycatch species (and discards) into account when scheduling effort (0=no, 1=yes)\n  \nSpatialBycatchAvoid     1    Whether using non-penalty/non-cap incentives to steer fleets away from areas where they discard the most (0=no, 1=yes)\n\n## Penalty tax ($/kg) - as disincentive on bycatch - one entry per fishery (needn't be identical, but is in AMS case).\n\n  \nFixedMinTa